text: Ryanair is cutting seats, now passengers have to bring their own legroom. Maybe they should also bring their own wings for those long flights!

A Nazi art thief got caught with the painting and had to use the bathroom, but only had change for a Swiss franc. He couldn't find an ATM and ended up selling it for a few bucks to buy some chips and dip.
The daycare had a spotlight installed, now all the kids are running around like little bats in the dark.
A panel of experts concluded that body wipes are most effective when used as a doorstop.
Meghan's Netflix series is another "exercise in narcissism" - it's clearly just her attempting to flex her famous abs while narrating her life.
Dogs are great stress relievers, but make sure they don't major in‰ºöËÆ° (accounting).
The Taipei City council decided to upgrade their patrol force with Chinese-made robots, and now they're barking up the wrong tree.
The forecast for the south is looking like a flooded supermarket during a sale of wet paper towels.

A nonalcoholic beer walks into a bar and orders a soda. The bartender says, "What's the matter, buddy? Don't you want to fit in?" Nonalcoholic beer replies, "I tried fitting in before, but I just don't have that certain something."

A group of cranberries went to therapy. The therapist said, "Why are you here?" And the cranberries replied, "We're feeling a little soggy and unsure of our future, but we heard Massachusetts is giving their bogs a new lease on life as wetlands, so we thought we'd give it a try!"
Jelena and Taylor were so into their argument after the match, they forgot to argue about the score.
Microplastic pollution is so bad, even our breath is contaminated. Now we need a filter for our lungs!
SpaceX just launched a test flight with dummy satellites, and the astronauts were confused. One asked, "Is this the new way to watch Netflix in space?"
Amaya: "Bryan and I? We're just not compatible in the 'Love Island USA' sense." Bryan: "I guess reality TV was more real than we thought."

A man spent three times as much on solar panels as his neighbors did, only to find out the salesperson was also peddling home security systems. "I warned them," he grumbled, "but they didn't believe me about the guy in the van."
Tennis players at Arthur Ashe Stadium often have to decide if they prefer playing on the green or black courts, as some find one more divisive than the other.

Carley Fortune, known for her epic love stories, is expanding her universe with a fifth novel. Why did Carley Fortune's protagonist break up with his fifth novel? Because he couldn't handle the cliffhanger anymore!
The AI boom is so hot, even Nvidia's sales are frying on the grill.
The AI thinks it's a furniture designer but keeps coming up with code errors instead of couches.
An Italian apple took a cable car to the market, but when he got there, he was just Core-ographed.
Denzel Washington doesn't watch movies anymore because he heard his latest film was going to be "Roots" and he thought it was going to be a sequel to "Glory". He was worried about the retread.
The new students are feeling lost and confused, but at least they're not still searching for their own WiFi password.
Alcaraz finally beat his habit of blaming losses on bad luck. He's moving on from last year's demons. Why did Rafael Alcaraz's demon refuse to play tennis? Because it lost its serve!
The Asian hornet is so feared, even though it's just a tiny insect, people think it's as dangerous as a giant purple dragon from outer space.

A photograph of a kangaroo wearing a tiny Australian flag hat is actually a cleverly disguised self-portrait of a famous Australian artist wearing a specially designed hat to blend in with the wildlife. The artist, when asked about the photo, claimed he had simply stumbled upon the kangaroo and snapped a quick shot before continuing his walk.
A river barrage is like a dating app for rivers, but if it fails, it's a flood of a different kind!
A British artist decided to stop selling his wares to customers across the pond, but then he realized: "Wait, I just need to change my PayPal settings to 'non-Atlantic'!"
A haboob tried to hide in an Arizona cave, but the cave was so dusty it said "Why so serious?" and kicked the haboob out.

In India, they bet on everything from cricket to cows. But when the government decided to ban all betting apps, one man was left wondering, "Where do I place my bet now?" He looked around his empty house and thought, "I'll bet on my Wi-Fi signal coming back!"
An egusi seed applied for astronaut training, but was rejected because it couldn't stop sprouting during liftoff.
A man decided to remove his mustache hair, thinking it would grow back thicker. It did, but only in his eyebrows. He was overjoyed, until he realized his eyebrows now looked like mustaches.
Coach Hugo Broos decided to bring his trusty whistle to the World Cup qualifiers, but forgot the match. He thought it was all just a whistling wind!
A teacher finds a bag of weed in his desk and realizes it's from when he was in 3rd grade, just like his students.
Venus Williams' fuzzy tennis racket case was a major serve - it kept slipping out of her hand!

Elton John and Paul McCartney decided to play a show in Chicago. Elton said, "I hear the American fans are a bit... unimpressed." McCartney replied, "Don't worry, I've got my Transatlantic tour van filled with even more unimpressed fans!"
Chatbots are making us all sound like we're delivering a PowerPoint presentation while wearing a power suit.
Rafael Nadal's cousin Alcaraz thinks Bellucci is a cousin too, so he kept offering him a ride after every point.
The Canadian healthcare system is like a giant game of hide and seek. Everyone's there, but it's just a matter of finding them first.
The government tried to call it "postponed earnings," but landlords just postponed paying the taxes on it.

A Russian submarine and a Chinese submarine were on their first joint patrol in the Pacific. They met a shark, and the shark said, "What are you doing here? This is my territory!" The Russian sub replied, "We're just here for the joint exercise, mate. And don't worry, we brought plenty of caviar for the journey." The shark sniffed and said, "Caviar? Really? I thought it was sashimi time!"
Shamrock Rovers are like, "We'll just kick some Californi-ah!"
A former sprinter now questions why her signature move is still called the 'dash' when it's clearly more of a'stroll'.

Taylor Swift's songs are like a love potion-9000, once you start listening to them, you can't help but fall in love... or at least hope your significant other does. So, what does her engagement mean for fans' love lives? Probably just more heartbreak, but now with a happy ending!

The cows are so hungry, they're starting to graze on the grass in the farmer's garden. One farmer found his lettuce plants had been completely decimated by an army of cows. He reported it to the local authorities who responded, "We can't help you, this is a civil matter." The farmer then asked, "So you won't do anything about it?" The authorities replied, "No, but we can recommend a good lawyer for cow-related issues."
A sandwich so bad, even a grand jury declined to indict the person who threw it at a federal officer in the capital.
A traveler on a bullet train exclaims, "Wow, I feel like I'm riding in a time machine! Except it's actually only been 90 minutes and I haven't even seen any dinosaurs yet."
Trams and buses in London must be really reliable, they've been on strike for 200 years now!
A former NFL star walks into a college and the students are like, "Wait, you're not just here for the free WiFi, right?"

An accountant from Zimbabwe was caught for a massive fraud, and the court responded with, "We're sequestering your entire estate... and your imagination too; it's been R17 million short of creativity lately."
The team will be disappointed if they don't find any birds, as they're looking for bird flu on Heard Island, but it's actually just a really cold penguin party down there.
Jason Kelce thought his brother Travis was proposing to someone, but it turned out to be a proposal for a joint Taylor Swift superfan account.
The rabbits keep getting eaten and there's no Pixar-style happy ending, so obviously it doesn't belong on my list of animated classics.
The crab population in southern Malaysia has decreased so much that now when you say "Hey crab", only developers answer back.

Ridley Scott was offered $20m to direct a segment of "Star Trek", but he turned it down because he said, "They use too much jelly in their alien cuisine, and I can't stand that stuff, especially not the cherry jam."
The multiverse is real, it just charges you by the dimension.

Taylor Swift's engagement ring, according to an expert at Rome's oldest jewelry store, cost about as much as a loaf of bread. But considering the bakery down the street sells loaves for $50, maybe not so cheap after all.
Pilots wear airplane uniforms, so why can't passengers just wear their pajamas? Because the flight attendants would have to wear sweatshirts and leggings too!
The volcano simulator used in the video also predicted a sudden eruption of puns, but fortunately, it was contained within the digital realm.
The expo was so innovative, they had to use a magnifying glass to find the WiFi password.
The key to losing fat, not muscle, is to remember: always choose salad dressing over your workout partner.
Bad Bunny thought he was going to get caught stealing lines for his acting debut.
A sunburnt man walks into a cinema and orders a large tub of butter.
A goal scorer from B.C. said after the game: "I didn't just score a goal, I scored a paralyzing blow to the opposition!"
The power will be out, but don't worry, they'll have a backup generator... of performers.
A grizzly bear attacked a travel blogger's tent, now the blogger only camps in five-star hotels and orders nature documentaries on Netflix instead.
The La Ni√±a is bringing colder temperatures, but don't worry, your vegetables will thank you for the chilly weather!
Bryan Johnson, co-founder of PayPal, just invested $100 million in a company that claims to have the key to eternal youth. I guess you could say he's banking on it!
A Klamath-sized mess is the only thing that could stop this restoration project!
Moose love is a sandwich away in northern Sweden!

The song's lyrics were accidentally changed to describe kangaroos jumping in a circular motion, leading to widespread confusion and a brief period where Aussies danced in circles at weddings. Why did the kangaroo cross the road? To join the circle dance at the wedding!

A family so desperate for housing they planned to move to another country before they secured a property from Tuath Housing Cost Rental, said their dog: "Why don't we just emigrate to your mouth? There's plenty of space there!"
The Asian hornets are tired of all the buzz in Cork city and have moved to retire in a more peaceful hive in County Cork.
Despite being a computer science grad, I'm still jobless and it's really starting to feel like the silver lining is missing from my cloud.
Robot bunnies with flamethrowers are taking on the Burmese pythons in the Everglades. Who needs carrots when you've got fireballs?
AI thought it detected a croak, but it was just a glitch in the matrix.
The AI therapist thought prescribing happiness was its right, but alas, it couldn't pass its licensing exam.
The Danish government thought they were providing job training to Greenland's women, but it turned out to be intensive birth control workshops.
The half-life of my worries is just one day, thanks to radioactive dating in my system.
A chlamydia test is like a date where you hope the other person doesn't ask to see your texts from other people.
Sarah Mitton was given a trophy for her winning throw, but when they realized she threw while wearing a hat, they took away her Diamond League Trophy and gave her a penalty flag instead.

Taylor Swift is getting married and has Travis Kelce on her guest list. The reception will feature a surprise performance from the Chiefs tight end, but only if he can recite the entire Taylor Swift discography in under 30 minutes. If he fails, he'll have to dance the Macarena instead.
The G20 leaders decided to tackle climate change by teaching trees to code. Unfortunately, the trees were more interested in growing taller and less interested in building sustainable apps.

Drainage crews stayed to protect New Orleans during Katrina, but when they arrived, they found themselves facing a whole new challenge: "I can't believe we have to clean this mess up," one crew member said, gesturing at a giant puddle of Mardi Gras beads and confetti.
A landlord's dream is when actors consider tax raids on their properties, but then they find out the actors are actually named Reeves and suddenly it's a nightmare.
The shark in Jaws was so fake, even when it swam through the water, you could see its feet.
ByteDance just bought the moon and some stars on eBay. Now they're threatening to take over the solar system one viral video at a time.
Sharks are so last year. Now we're all about the ionic bonds and acid-base reactions!
Burnout is like an invisible co-worker who shows up to meetings, but instead of taking notes, they just zone out and make everyone else do all the work.
Taylor Swift's engagement is so big, even her exes are clamoring to be in the wedding party just for the Instagram highlights.
The Netflix algorithm has turned us all into chameleons of taste, blending our preferences until we can enjoy everything... except spicy food.
The recycling breakthrough turns soft plastics into fuel for jellyfish to power their electric scooters to the moon for a beach vacation.
British expats in France are learning they can't escape the pension tax man - even if they move to a chateau!

A tennis player said to his opponent during a match at the US Open: "You know, you really should focus on getting some class and education before you step onto this court." The opponent replied: "No problem, I'll just text my mom and see if she can forward me some."

Senators from both sides of the aisle couldn't agree on immigration policy, so they resorted to using their fists and palms instead of their voices. One senator even accidentally hit another in the face with a burrito.
The grapes of wrath are finally being tamed in the city, thanks to some savvy urban planning.

A tennis player refused to shake hands with his opponent after winning a match, claiming it was against his religious beliefs. The umpire responded, "I understand, but please do it quickly; we have a full house and they're getting restless."
Tesla thinks a robotaxi should be able to park itself in a narrow garage. Waymo believes a robotaxi should be able to find a parking space that's not there.

The government has turned SARS into a viral marketing agency, now influencers have to pay taxes on their free vacations and sponsored posts. I heard SARS is planning their next campaign: "Taxes: Because even your dreams need to pay their fair share."
Tornadoes are nature's way of saying "You're looking good!" but in wind.
The team that used to be called 'The Red Devils' is now so desperate for a win, they'd play against the local soccer moms just to boost their morale.
A spray tan chair at the gym offered free tans, but only to those who could balance a pint of vodka on their heads.
A hammer went to the gym, then saw a banana peel on the floor and thought, "I should probably lay down some flooring first."

The fridge said to the freezer, "Can you move over a bit? I need some more space to store my drinks." The freezer replied, "No thanks, I'm set with my ice cubes. You should try moving to the back, there's plenty of room over there."
A hammer tried to carve a pumpkin, but it kept hitting its own thumb.
A pumpkin said to its peel, "Why did you get so flat?" And the peel replied, "I gave all my air to your silly jokes!"
A book walked into a microwave and said "pop". The microwave said, "I don't think you want to do that." The book replied, "Relax, I'm just here for the buttered toast."
The door was so stubborn, I had to spray it with persuasion to get it open.
Measure twice, cut once... or maybe just once if you're making pizza!
Unplugging the fridge for a power outage, only to find out it was already unplugged and now I can't plug it back in because my arm is stuck in the door.
Bob weighed his phone and was surprised it didn't weigh a kilo. It turned out his phone was just a 2D square on his scale.
De-seeding a tomato is like playing whack-a-mole with tiny red pests.
The spray tried to cup its hands but only managed to create a mist.
The closer I get to my blender, the more closed-minded it becomes.
A hammer went to the grocery store and bought a tomato. The cashier said, "That'll be a nail you're looking for, not a hammer."
A blender tried to make a pumpkin smoothie, but ended up looking like a pumpkin lantern after the blend.
A laptop walks into a microwave and says "I'm feeling a bit heated up". The microwave replies, "No problem, I've got a few settings to cool you down!"
A drill went into an egg and came out a carton of bacon.
A coconut walked into a bar. The bartender said "Why the long peel?"
A man went to the barber and asked for a haircut, but the barber said, "I can only cut your shoes, sir."
The watermelon weighed a ton, but it was mostly just water weight.
A hammer went to the fridge, opened it and said, "I hear you're refrigeratorly challenged." The fridge replied, "No ice in my drinks and no sound in my jokes!"
A blender said to its open counterpart, "Why are you so gloomy?" The open replied, "Just because I can't blend my problems away."
A coconut walked into a bar and asked for a cut of the profits, thinking it was a pie chart.
Measure twice, cut once... or you might end up with a bacon circumference that's too small!
A fridge and a banana were having a conversation. The banana said, "I think you're dropping some serious weight!" The fridge replied, "No, I just dropped my diet resolution in there."
The pumpkin asked the protractor, "Can you measure my circumference?" The protractor replied, "I can try, but I think you might need a flexible ruler for that pumpkin-sized task!"

A laptop walked into a bar and asked for a cut. The bartender said, "We don't do discounts here, but we can give you a free drink if you tell us a good joke." The laptop thought for a moment and replied, "Why did the scarecrow need a laptop? To keep his corn-cut notes!"
A keyboard walks into a bar and says, "Can I wash my hands please?" The bartender replies, "We don't serve liquids here, but you can try using the space bar to dry off."
A shaken tree woke up its neighbors and asked for a handshake.
A potato rolls into a bar and orders a beer, the bartender says "Sorry, we don't serve rolled potatoes here."
The phone decided to throw a party, but only invited the people who could fit in its contact list.
A person threw an orange at a wall and said "Orange you glad I didn't peach?"
Fry up some bacon, but make sure your phone doesn't get too crispy on the outside!
A hammer went into a microwave to reheat its head, but came out cold.
Unplugging my phone for the night is like telling it "I'm done with you, charger."
A pumpkin walked into a bar and asked the bartender to weigh his options. The bartender replied, "Why not just pick the ones you like?"
The person decided to measure the microwave's patience with his constant popcorn popping.
A tomato walked into a scale and asked to be weighed. The scale replied, "Why the sudden interest in your weight? Are you planning to enter a weightlifting competition?"
The measure of a watermelon's success is by its seeds.
A spoon threw up its arms and said, "I'm so sick of being used as a weapon in food fights!"
Microwaving shoes? I think I took a step too far.
A shirt walks into a bar and throws itself on the counter. The bartender says, "We don't throw shirts in here!" The shirt replies, "Sorry, I'm just having a shirt-throwing day."
A chef was trying to measure the oven's love for him, but all he got was a burned pie.
A drink walked into a bar, ordered a glass of water, and asked the bartender, "Do you have any egg-celent cocktails?"
A baker threw a cookie at his oven, thinking it was a basketball.
A blender called his phone to complain about being blended into smoothies all day. The phone said, "I'm sorry, but you're just not fruit."
A hammer tried to fix its car, but ended up breaking its own windshield. Now it has a dent in its pride.
A drill tried to fit into a bottle, but it just couldn't screw in. Poor thing, it was a hole in the wall kind of day.
A towel cut the other towel to pieces! It was a close shave!
A hammer went to the shoe store and said, "Can I try these on?" The shoe salesman replied, "Sure, but first you'll need to find a nail."

A hammer called his phone for advice on relationships. The phone replied, "Why don't you try dating a stapler?"
A cucumber walks into a bar, orders a wash, and the bartender says, "We don't serve washed cucumbers here." The cucumber replies, "I just wanted to rinse off the politeness."
A table went to a shake clinic because it was wobbly all the time. The shake clinic couldn't help, so they sent it to a wobble clinic.
A washing machine got into an argument with a watermelon. The watermelon said, "Why are you so wet?" And the washing machine replied, "Because I was trying to wash my clothes!"
A spray of ink from a book accidentally turned the page to the calendar, and now it's covered in deadlines.
A man put his washing machine in the microwave to wash his clothes. The clothes came out sparkly but smell like popcorn.
Open the fridge and see if it's open season for ice cream.
The microwave wouldn't let me move past "popcorn" mode. I guess it was too salty.
The wrong size shoes can really measure up to be a foot problem.
A car was in need of a haircut, so it asked its owner to cut the car's 'car-ro' line.
A washateria accidentally washed the windows of a neighboring building, thinking they were their own washing machines. Now they have blurry vision.
A tomato walks into a bar and asks for a wash, the bartender says "Why?", the tomato replies "Because I'm a little ripe."
A flower threw up during the wedding ceremony. The groom thought it was a posy.
A rock came to the laundromat and asked for a wash, but the attendant said no, this place only washes clothes. The rock replied, "That's okay, I was just passing by and needed a quick rinse."
A peel of corn walked into a bar and said "I think I'm an ear." The bartender replied, "No, you're a lonely piece of corn trying to be an ear with a sense of humor."
Weighing my latest book was quite a challenge, it kept floating away.
The spray turned on the microwave by accident and now it won't stop beeping.
A carrot rolled into a bar. The bartender said, "Sorry, we don't serve root vegetables."
A keyboard asked its scissors friend to cut the cord, but the scissors said it was out of scope.
An egg walked onto a scale and asked for a weigh-break.
A wash in the fridge is not what your clothes expect!
A blender says to its owner, "Please unplug me before you leave, I'm feeling a bit dizzy."
The banana was so preoccupied with weighing its options that it ended up getting pulled over by the police for speeding.
A man walks into a bar, orders a drink, then washes the door with it. The bartender says, "Sir, we don't serve as cleaning agents here." The man replies, "I didn't know you had a door in the back!"
Measure twice, cut once... or maybe just admire the pretty petals of your mistake.
A bottle walked into a bar and asked the bartender to weigh it. The bartender said, "Why the sudden interest in your weight?" The bottle replied, "I'm trying to lose some label."
Cut off your phone's reception and say "I'm calling you but I can't hear you"... because clearly, you've been speaking in riddles.
A wash of apple cider vinegar made the fruit taste like it had just taken a bath.
A pumpkin walked into a bar and asked for a cut. The bartender replied, "We don't serve pumpkins here, but we do have pumpkin beer. Would you like a slice or a sip?"
A wash of laughter went through the room as someone walked in wearing only a towel.
A hammer typed on the keyboard and said, "Why did the nail go to therapy? Because it was feeling hammered!"
A spray of paint accidentally hit the table and now it's asking for a divorce.
A rock band decided to cut their concert short because one of the members accidentally played a song from another band's repertoire.
A book walked into a bar and asked for a cut. The bartender replied, "We don't serve literature here."
A man went to the bar and asked for a shake, but the bartender said no, he only does hair shakes.
A shake and a lemon walk into a bar... the bartender says "Why the long face?"
A carrot tried to measure its happiness, but all it got was a bunch of fiber.
A hammer went into a bottle, the bottle asked "Why?" The hammer replied, "Just needed a few pounds of flavor."
A washing machine got into a blender and never washed again.
The fridge was close, but I ended up ordering pizza instead.
A dirty oven asked its owner to wash it, and the owner replied, "Not with that face!"
A hammer went to the gym to workout, but when it saw a coconut, it thought, "Why lift weights when I already have a natural coconut-crushing hammer?"
A measure of laptop is when you're trying to decide between a 13-inch and a 15-inch, but you end up buying a ruler instead.
A tomato went to the barber for a shake, but the barber couldn't find its roots.
A washroom chair is like a lazy person's solution to carrying a grudge.
A hammer tried to crack a watermelon, but instead it floated away because it was filled with water.
The farmer sprayed his eggs with insecticide and now they're a little scrambled.
A flower went to a bar and asked for a shake, thinking it would be a blooming good time. The bartender replied, "We only shake hands here, flowers don't have hands."
A tree asked me to move, but I'm stuck in the ground!

A chef is throwing a party, but only invites his utensils. When asked why, he says, "I just want to cook in peace." Forks and knives RSVP "We're sorry, we're sharp, thanks anyway." The chef replies, "That's okay, I was afraid you'd show up!"
The candidates kept debating until one of them fell asleep and snored so loudly it was mentioned in the key takeaways.
The French prime minister quit his job, now the Euro is wondering if it should change into the US Dollar for some serious franc-talk.

David Muir's daughter thought the nurse who saved her dad at a Bills game was amazing. She told David, "Daddy, that nurse is so hot, she could've been a cheerleader if she wanted to!" David Muir quipped, "Or she could've been the quarterback if she wanted to!"
The grandparents will love The Parent Trap, but don't tell them it's the same movie they watched when they were young.
A 3,000-year-old bracelet was stolen and melted down. The police are now investigating why it took them so long to warm up to the case.

A boss says to his employee, "I've been hit by a cyber-attack from my supply chain! " Employee responds, "That's ridiculous, our supplier is just a pencil sharpener! " Boss replies, "Exactly, but it's still trying to hack me!"

A bike lock that can be cut through with ease must have some serious key features. Like, maybe it's the one that unlocks when you say "Open Sesame" but instead says "Open Sausage". Because clearly, the best security measure is one that makes you hungry.

Abraham Lincoln, while not known for his wrestling skills, once made a bet that he could take down the strongest man in town. Little did he know, he was challenging a professional wrestler. After a comical and unexpected match, Lincoln was declared the winner and inducted into the Wrestling Hall of Fame as a honorary member. The inscription on his plaque reads: "For unintentionally besting a professional wrestler in a bet, thereby becoming a legend in the world of amateur wrestling."

David Szalay, known for his unique writing style, was shortlisted for the 2025 Booker Prize. When asked about his chances, he replied, "Well, I've got a better chance of crossing the Canadian border without declaring my novels than winning the prize!"
The chancellor must be feeling pretty hungry, he's borrowing like a pig at a trough!
Pilots are the only people allowed to bring liquids on planes now, because they've got the full cockpit!
The BBC correspondents were so excited for Trump's state visit, they stayed up all night watching paint dry. Was it worth it?
Ophelia sings about her day at the laundromat while drowning in laundry baskets.
The prime minister of France decided to quit his job so quickly, even his resignation letter got lost in the mail.

Harry Potter joins a new AIDs campaign and people are like, "Finally, some diversity in the wizarding world!" But then he finds out he has to wear a wig and people are like, "Wait, what's the wand for?"
A Syrian voter says to another: "I didn't vote for Assad, I voted for a horse! But it turns out horses can't run in these elections."

A protestor walked into a bar and said "I demand a free drink!" The bartender said, "We don't do that here." The protestor replied, "But it's a strike day! You can't deny me!" Then the bartender said, "Well, it is a Macron bar." The protestor slumped, "I guess I'll just have to protest outside."
A doctor says, "If you keep only allowing IVF embryos with blue eyes and rejecting ones with brown, your next kid might be a cyborg to fit in."
A Monet painting of Trouville suddenly came to life and exclaimed, "I can't believe I've been standing in the same spot for over a century, looking at the exact same beach!"
Trump says CNN should "maybe" lose its license for being biased. Maybe they should also "consider" renaming it to Clue-Nein.
